attributes.Long form description:
The student disassembles a table. He starts by slightly unscrewing all the hex socket heads from the table. After that, he unscrews the 
eight top hex socket heads that hold the table. Once the student releases the table, he continues to unscrew the bottom eight hex socket heads that hold the shelf together. The student places the shelf on the table to finish the task.

attributes.Transcription: So hello thank you for agreeing for taking part in the trail.
In front of you, you will see the Knarrevik bedside table. Your task will be to please disassemble the table.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the first leg lightly.

attributes.Transcription: So first, lightly unscrew the screw.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the second leg lightly.
The student unscrews the third leg lightly.
The student unscrews the fourth leg lightly.
The student disassembles the top shelf of the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Before removing the top shelf, the student should place the unit horizontally

attributes.Transcription: Before removing the top shelf, please place the unit horizontally.
